  27 class SchemaError(Exception):
  28     """ Raised when the validation schema is missing, has the wrong format or
  29         contains errors. """
  30

  34 class DefinitionSchema(MutableMapping):
  35     """ A dict-subclass for caching of validated schemas. """
  36 
  37     def __new__(cls, *args, **kwargs):
  38         if 'SchemaValidator' not in globals():
  39             global SchemaValidator
  40             SchemaValidator = validator_factory('SchemaValidator', SchemaValidatorMixin)
  41             types_mapping = SchemaValidator.types_mapping.copy()
  42             types_mapping.update(
  43                 {
  44                     'callable': TypeDefinition('callable', (Callable,), ()),
  45                     'hashable': TypeDefinition('hashable', (Hashable,), ()),
  46                 }
  47             )
  48             SchemaValidator.types_mapping = types_mapping
  49 
  50         return super(DefinitionSchema, cls).__new__(cls)
  51 
  52     def __init__(self, validator, schema):
  53         """
  54         :param validator: An instance of Validator-(sub-)class that uses this
  55                           schema.
  56         :param schema: A definition-schema as ``dict``. Defaults to an empty
  57                        one.
  58         """
  59         if not isinstance(validator, get_Validator_class()):
  60             raise RuntimeError('validator argument must be a Validator-' 'instance.')
  61         self.validator = validator
  62 
  63         if isinstance(schema, _str_type):
  64             schema = validator.schema_registry.get(schema, schema)
  65 
  66         if not isinstance(schema, Mapping):
  67             try:
  68                 schema = dict(schema)
  69             except Exception:
  70                 raise SchemaError(errors.SCHEMA_ERROR_DEFINITION_TYPE.format(schema))
  71 
  72         self.validation_schema = SchemaValidationSchema(validator)
  73         self.schema_validator = SchemaValidator(
  74             None,
  75             allow_unknown=self.validation_schema,
  76             error_handler=errors.SchemaErrorHandler,
  77             target_schema=schema,
  78             target_validator=validator,
  79         )
  80 
  81         schema = self.expand(schema)
  82         self.validate(schema)
  83         self.schema = schema
  84 
  85     def __delitem__(self, key):
  86         _new_schema = self.schema.copy()
  87         try:
  88             del _new_schema[key]
  89         except ValueError:
  90             raise SchemaError("Schema has no field '%s' defined" % key)
  91         except Exception as e:
  92             raise e
  93         else:
  94             del self.schema[key]
  95 
  96     def __getitem__(self, item):
  97         return self.schema[item]
  98 
  99     def __iter__(self):
 100         return iter(self.schema)
 101 
 102     def __len__(self):
 103         return len(self.schema)
 104 
 105     def __repr__(self):
 106         return str(self)
 107 
 108     def __setitem__(self, key, value):
 109         value = self.expand({0: value})[0]
 110         self.validate({key: value})
 111         self.schema[key] = value
 112 
 113     def __str__(self):
 114         if hasattr(self, "schema"):
 115             return str(self.schema)
 116         else:
 117             return "No schema data is set yet."
 118 
 119     def copy(self):
 120         return self.__class__(self.validator, self.schema.copy())
 121 
 122     @classmethod
 123     def expand(cls, schema):
 124         try:
 125             schema = cls._expand_logical_shortcuts(schema)
 126             schema = cls._expand_subschemas(schema)
 127         except Exception:
 128             pass
 129 
 130         # TODO remove this with the next major release
 131         schema = cls._rename_deprecated_rulenames(schema)
 132 
 133         return schema
 134 
 135     @classmethod
 136     def _expand_logical_shortcuts(cls, schema):
 137         """ Expand agglutinated rules in a definition-schema.
 138 
 139         :param schema: The schema-definition to expand.
 140         :return: The expanded schema-definition.
 141         """
 142 
 143         def is_of_rule(x):
 144             return isinstance(x, _str_type) and x.startswith(
 145                 ('allof_', 'anyof_', 'noneof_', 'oneof_')
 146             )
 147 
 148         for field, rules in schema.items():
 149             for of_rule in [x for x in rules if is_of_rule(x)]:
 150                 operator, rule = of_rule.split('_', 1)
 151                 rules.update({operator: []})
 152                 for value in rules[of_rule]:
 153                     rules[operator].append({rule: value})
 154                 del rules[of_rule]
 155         return schema
 156 
 157     @classmethod
 158     def _expand_subschemas(cls, schema):
 159         def has_schema_rule():
 160             return isinstance(schema[field], Mapping) and 'schema' in schema[field]
 161 
 162         def has_mapping_schema():
 163             """ Tries to determine heuristically if the schema-constraints are
 164                 aimed to mappings. """
 165             try:
 166                 return all(
 167                     isinstance(x, Mapping) for x in schema[field]['schema'].values()
 168                 )
 169             except TypeError:
 170                 return False
 171 
 172         for field in schema:
 173             if not has_schema_rule():
 174                 pass
 175             elif has_mapping_schema():
 176                 schema[field]['schema'] = cls.expand(schema[field]['schema'])
 177             else:  # assumes schema-constraints for a sequence
 178                 schema[field]['schema'] = cls.expand({0: schema[field]['schema']})[0]
 179 
 180             # TODO remove the last two values in the tuple with the next major release
 181             for rule in ('keysrules', 'valuesrules', 'keyschema', 'valueschema'):
 182                 if rule in schema[field]:
 183                     schema[field][rule] = cls.expand({0: schema[field][rule]})[0]
 184 
 185             for rule in ('allof', 'anyof', 'items', 'noneof', 'oneof'):
 186                 if rule in schema[field]:
 187                     if not isinstance(schema[field][rule], Sequence):
 188                         continue
 189                     new_rules_definition = []
 190                     for item in schema[field][rule]:
 191                         new_rules_definition.append(cls.expand({0: item})[0])
 192                     schema[field][rule] = new_rules_definition
 193         return schema
 194 
 195     def get(self, item, default=None):
 196         return self.schema.get(item, default)
 197 
 198     def items(self):
 199         return self.schema.items()
 200 
 201     def update(self, schema):
 202         try:
 203             schema = self.expand(schema)
 204             _new_schema = self.schema.copy()
 205             _new_schema.update(schema)
 206             self.validate(_new_schema)
 207         except ValueError:
 208             raise SchemaError(errors.SCHEMA_ERROR_DEFINITION_TYPE.format(schema))
 209         except Exception as e:
 210             raise e
 211         else:
 212             self.schema = _new_schema
 213 
 214     # TODO remove with next major release
 215     @staticmethod
 216     def _rename_deprecated_rulenames(schema):
 217         for field, rules in schema.items():
 218 
 219             if isinstance(rules, str):  # registry reference
 220                 continue
 221 
 222             for old, new in (
 223                 ('keyschema', 'keysrules'),
 224                 ('validator', 'check_with'),
 225                 ('valueschema', 'valuesrules'),
 226             ):
 227 
 228                 if old not in rules:
 229                     continue
 230 
 231                 if new in rules:
 232                     raise RuntimeError(
 233                         "The rule '{new}' is also present with its old "
 234                         "name '{old}' in the same set of rules."
 235                     )
 236 
 237                 warn(
 238                     "The rule '{old}' was renamed to '{new}'. The old name will "
 239                     "not be available in the next major release of "
 240                     "Cerberus.".format(old=old, new=new),
 241                     DeprecationWarning,
 242                 )
 243                 schema[field][new] = schema[field][old]
 244                 schema[field].pop(old)
 245 
 246         return schema
 247 
 248     def regenerate_validation_schema(self):
 249         self.validation_schema = SchemaValidationSchema(self.validator)
 250 
 251     def validate(self, schema=None):
 252         """ Validates a schema that defines rules against supported rules.
 253 
 254         :param schema: The schema to be validated as a legal cerberus schema
 255                        according to the rules of the assigned Validator object.
 256                        Raises a :class:`~cerberus.base.SchemaError` when an invalid
 257                        schema is encountered. """
 258         if schema is None:
 259             schema = self.schema
 260         _hash = (mapping_hash(schema), mapping_hash(self.validator.types_mapping))
 261         if _hash not in self.validator._valid_schemas:
 262             self._validate(schema)
 263             self.validator._valid_schemas.add(_hash)
 264 
 265     def _validate(self, schema):
 266         if isinstance(schema, _str_type):
 267             schema = self.validator.schema_registry.get(schema, schema)
 268 
 269         if schema is None:
 270             raise SchemaError(errors.SCHEMA_ERROR_MISSING)
 271 
 272         schema = copy(schema)
 273         for field in schema:
 274             if isinstance(schema[field], _str_type):
 275                 schema[field] = rules_set_registry.get(schema[field], schema[field])
 276 
 277         if not self.schema_validator(schema, normalize=False):
 278             raise SchemaError(self.schema_validator.errors)

 281 class UnvalidatedSchema(DefinitionSchema):
 282     def __init__(self, schema={}):
 283         if not isinstance(schema, Mapping):
 284             schema = dict(schema)
 285         self.schema = schema
 286 
 287     def validate(self, schema):
 288         pass
 289 
 290     def copy(self):
 291         # Override ancestor's copy, because
 292         # UnvalidatedSchema does not have .validator:
 293         return self.__class__(self.schema.copy())

 296 class SchemaValidationSchema(UnvalidatedSchema):
 297     def __init__(self, validator):
 298         self.schema = {
 299             'allow_unknown': False,
 300             'schema': validator.rules,
 301             'type': 'dict',
 302         }

 305 class SchemaValidatorMixin(object):
 306     """ This validator mixin provides mechanics to validate schemas passed to a Cerberus
 307         validator. """
 308 
 309     def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
 310         kwargs.setdefault('known_rules_set_refs', set())
 311         kwargs.setdefault('known_schema_refs', set())
 312         super(SchemaValidatorMixin, self).__init__(*args, **kwargs)
 313 
 314     @property
 315     def known_rules_set_refs(self):
 316         """ The encountered references to rules set registry items. """
 317         return self._config['known_rules_set_refs']
 318 
 319     @property
 320     def known_schema_refs(self):
 321         """ The encountered references to schema registry items. """
 322         return self._config['known_schema_refs']
 323 
 324     @property
 325     def target_schema(self):
 326         """ The schema that is being validated. """
 327         return self._config['target_schema']
 328 
 329     @property
 330     def target_validator(self):
 331         """ The validator whose schema is being validated. """
 332         return self._config['target_validator']
 333 
 334     def _check_with_bulk_schema(self, field, value):
 335         # resolve schema registry reference
 336         if isinstance(value, _str_type):
 337             if value in self.known_rules_set_refs:
 338                 return
 339             else:
 340                 self.known_rules_set_refs.add(value)
 341             definition = self.target_validator.rules_set_registry.get(value)
 342             if definition is None:
 343                 self._error(field, 'Rules set definition %s not found.' % value)
 344                 return
 345             else:
 346                 value = definition
 347 
 348         _hash = (
 349             mapping_hash({'turing': value}),
 350             mapping_hash(self.target_validator.types_mapping),
 351         )
 352         if _hash in self.target_validator._valid_schemas:
 353             return
 354 
 355         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 356             document_crumb=field,
 357             allow_unknown=False,
 358             schema=self.target_validator.rules,
 359         )
 360         validator(value, normalize=False)
 361         if validator._errors:
 362             self._error(validator._errors)
 363         else:
 364             self.target_validator._valid_schemas.add(_hash)
 365 
 366     def _check_with_dependencies(self, field, value):
 367         if isinstance(value, _str_type):
 368             pass
 369         elif isinstance(value, Mapping):
 370             validator = self._get_child_validator(
 371                 document_crumb=field,
 372                 schema={'valuesrules': {'type': 'list'}},
 373                 allow_unknown=True,
 374             )
 375             if not validator(value, normalize=False):
 376                 self._error(validator._errors)
 377         elif isinstance(value, Sequence):
 378             if not all(isinstance(x, Hashable) for x in value):
 379                 path = self.document_path + (field,)
 380                 self._error(path, 'All dependencies must be a hashable type.')
 381 
 382     def _check_with_items(self, field, value):
 383         for i, schema in enumerate(value):
 384             self._check_with_bulk_schema((field, i), schema)
 385 
 386     def _check_with_schema(self, field, value):
 387         try:
 388             value = self._handle_schema_reference_for_validator(field, value)
 389         except _Abort:
 390             return
 391 
 392         _hash = (mapping_hash(value), mapping_hash(self.target_validator.types_mapping))
 393         if _hash in self.target_validator._valid_schemas:
 394             return
 395 
 396         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 397             document_crumb=field, schema=None, allow_unknown=self.root_allow_unknown
 398         )
 399         validator(self._expand_rules_set_refs(value), normalize=False)
 400         if validator._errors:
 401             self._error(validator._errors)
 402         else:
 403             self.target_validator._valid_schemas.add(_hash)
 404 
 405     def _check_with_type(self, field, value):
 406         value = set((value,)) if isinstance(value, _str_type) else set(value)
 407         invalid_constraints = value - set(self.target_validator.types)
 408         if invalid_constraints:
 409             self._error(
 410                 field, 'Unsupported types: {}'.format(', '.join(invalid_constraints))
 411             )
 412 
 413     def _expand_rules_set_refs(self, schema):
 414         result = {}
 415         for k, v in schema.items():
 416             if isinstance(v, _str_type):
 417                 result[k] = self.target_validator.rules_set_registry.get(v)
 418             else:
 419                 result[k] = v
 420         return result
 421 
 422     def _handle_schema_reference_for_validator(self, field, value):
 423         if not isinstance(value, _str_type):
 424             return value
 425         if value in self.known_schema_refs:
 426             raise _Abort
 427 
 428         self.known_schema_refs.add(value)
 429         definition = self.target_validator.schema_registry.get(value)
 430         if definition is None:
 431             path = self.document_path + (field,)
 432             self._error(path, 'Schema definition {} not found.'.format(value))
 433             raise _Abort
 434         return definition
 435 
 436     def _validate_logical(self, rule, field, value):
 437         """ {'allowed': ('allof', 'anyof', 'noneof', 'oneof')} """
 438         if not isinstance(value, Sequence):
 439             self._error(field, errors.BAD_TYPE)
 440             return
 441 
 442         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 443             document_crumb=rule,
 444             allow_unknown=False,
 445             schema=self.target_validator.validation_rules,
 446         )
 447 
 448         for constraints in value:
 449             _hash = (
 450                 mapping_hash({'turing': constraints}),
 451                 mapping_hash(self.target_validator.types_mapping),
 452             )
 453             if _hash in self.target_validator._valid_schemas:
 454                 continue
 455 
 456             validator(constraints, normalize=False)
 457             if validator._errors:
 458                 self._error(validator._errors)
 459             else:
 460                 self.target_validator._valid_schemas.add(_hash)

 466 class Registry(object):
 467     """ A registry to store and retrieve schemas and parts of it by a name
 468     that can be used in validation schemas.
 469 
 470     :param definitions: Optional, initial definitions.
 471     :type definitions: any :term:`mapping` """
 472 
 473     def __init__(self, definitions={}):
 474         self._storage = {}
 475         self.extend(definitions)
 476 
 477     def add(self, name, definition):
 478         """ Register a definition to the registry. Existing definitions are
 479         replaced silently.
 480 
 481         :param name: The name which can be used as reference in a validation
 482                      schema.
 483         :type name: :class:`str`
 484         :param definition: The definition.
 485         :type definition: any :term:`mapping` """
 486         self._storage[name] = self._expand_definition(definition)
 487 
 488     def all(self):
 489         """ Returns a :class:`dict` with all registered definitions mapped to
 490         their name. """
 491         return self._storage
 492 
 493     def clear(self):
 494         """ Purge all definitions in the registry. """
 495         self._storage.clear()
 496 
 497     def extend(self, definitions):
 498         """ Add several definitions at once. Existing definitions are
 499         replaced silently.
 500 
 501         :param definitions: The names and definitions.
 502         :type definitions: a :term:`mapping` or an :term:`iterable` with
 503                            two-value :class:`tuple` s """
 504         for name, definition in dict(definitions).items():
 505             self.add(name, definition)
 506 
 507     def get(self, name, default=None):
 508         """ Retrieve a definition from the registry.
 509 
 510         :param name: The reference that points to the definition.
 511         :type name: :class:`str`
 512         :param default: Return value if the reference isn't registered. """
 513         return self._storage.get(name, default)
 514 
 515     def remove(self, *names):
 516         """ Unregister definitions from the registry.
 517 
 518         :param names: The names of the definitions that are to be
 519                       unregistered. """
 520         for name in names:
 521             self._storage.pop(name, None)
 522 
 523 
 524 class SchemaRegistry(Registry):
 525     @classmethod
 526     def _expand_definition(cls, definition):
 527         return DefinitionSchema.expand(definition)
 528 
 529 
 530 class RulesSetRegistry(Registry):
 531     @classmethod
 532     def _expand_definition(cls, definition):
 533         return DefinitionSchema.expand({0: definition})[0]
 534 
 535 
 536 schema_registry, rules_set_registry = SchemaRegistry(), RulesSetRegistry()
